<network>
  <name>talos-routed</name>
  <!--
    Bridge onto the host's br0 (eno1 -> ASUS RT-AX86U in Media Bridge mode),
    which presents true multi-MAC Ethernet over Wi-Fi. The VM sits directly
    on the HomeLab VLAN (192.168.10.0/24); no routed subnet, host routes, or
    egress NAT are involved anymore.

    The name stays "talos-routed" because the Omni libvirt provider's machine
    class references it; only the implementation changed.

    Gotcha that shaped this: the media bridge (proxy-STA) forwards unicast
    for secondary MACs but breaks DHCP for every MAC after the first — the
    VM therefore uses a static address from its Omni machine config, and
    this network must not carry ip/dhcp elements.
  -->
  <forward mode="bridge"/>
  <bridge name="br0"/>
</network>
